bug.short_desc: Test - Atom2 example - Line Height is not 1 pixel

long_desc.thetext:
The Atom2 example (and at least one other) looks different in FF1.5 and IE6. (see Screenshot) I figured out that setOverflow("hidden") fix that problem.
I hope this is helpful to someone !

These lines are no atoms. But otherwise you are right. I will try to integrate this into the new layout engine to automatically configure the line-height in such problematic cases. Also relevant because it's true in IE7, too.
Mhh, is seems that lineHeight = 0px doesn't help anymore to fulfill the requirements. Overflow=hidden indeed seems to work well. Ok, I've updated the example.
